  "terms": "By participating in this challenge you agree to:\n1. Not share your credentials with anyone\n2. Not attempt to access other teams' files or workspaces\n3. Submit only your own original work\n4. Maximum 3 official submissions per day\n5. Results are final as shown on the leaderboard",
  "pages": [
    {
      "id": 81031,
      "title": "Overview",
      "content": "# Waste Sorting Detection Challenge\n\n## About\nBuild the best object detection model to detect and classify waste objects from real conveyor belt images captured at a waste sorting facility. Compete across 19 waste categories.\n\n## Dataset\n- Train: 5,238 images \n- Test: 1,312 images\n\n## Sample Dataset\nDownload 50 sample images to visually explore the data:\nGo to the **files** tab → download **sample_dataset**.\n\n## Classes (19 total)\n| ID | Class | ID | Class |\n|----|-------|----|-------|\n| 0 | pet-bottle-clear | 10 | sachet |\n| 1 | pet-bottle-green | 11 | tetrapack |\n| 2 | ldpe-clear | 12 | cardboard-brown |\n| 3 | ldpe-hm | 13 | paper-box |\n| 4 | ldpe-black | 14 | coconut-shell |\n| 5 | hdpe-bottle | 15 | footwear |\n| 6 | metal-can | 16 | idpe-colored |\n| 7 | milk-packet | 17 | hard-plastic |\n| 8 | pp-bag | 18 | other |\n| 9 | mlp-packet | | |\n\n## Evaluation Metric\nPrimary metric: **mAP50** (COCO-style mean Average Precision at IoU=0.50)\n\n## How to Participate\n1. SSH into your assigned workstation (credentials shared separately)\n2. Train your model on the provided dataset at `/home/user/hackathon/Waste_sorting_dataset/`\n3. Generate predictions on the test set\n4. Submit using the provided `submit.py` script\n\n## Submission Format\nSubmit a ZIP file containing `predictions.json` in COCO detection format:\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"image_id\": 0,\n    \"category_id\": 0,\n    \"bbox\": [x, y, width, height],\n    \"score\": 0.95\n  }\n]\n```\n\n## Rules\n- Max 10 official submissions per day\n- Training only on provided dataset\n- No sharing of model weights between teams",
      "index": 0
    }
  ],
